org.jsonurl.j2se

Interface JavaValueFactory

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ValueFactory<Object,Object,List<Object>,List<Object>,Map<String,Object>,Map<String,Object>,Boolean,Number,Object,String>, ValueFactory.TransparentBuilder<Object,Object,List<Object>,Map<String,Object>,Boolean,Number,Object,String>

    public interface JavaValueFactory
extends ValueFactory.TransparentBuilder<Object,Object,List<Object>,Map<String,Object>,Boolean,Number,Object,String>
    A ValueFactory based on Java SE data types.

    The following singletons are available:

    • PRIMITIVE
    • DOUBLE
    • BIGMATH
    Since:
    2019-09-01
    Author:
    jsonurl.org, David MacCormack

    • Field Detail

      • PRIMITIVE

        static final JavaValueFactory PRIMITIVE
        A singleton instance of JavaValueFactory that stores numbers as boxed primitives.

        This factory uses an instance of Long for (most) numbers which fall between Long.MIN_VALUE and Long.MAX_VALUE, and an instance of Double for everything else.

      • DOUBLE

        static final JavaValueFactory DOUBLE
        A singleton instance of JavaValueFactory that uses instances of Double for all numbers.

      • BIGMATH

        static final JavaValueFactory BIGMATH
        A singleton instance of JavaValueFactory that uses BigInteger and BigDecimal when necessary.

        When using this factory, numbers without fractional parts that are too big to be stored in a Long will be stored in a BigInteger. Numbers with fractional parts that are too big to stored in a Double will be stored in a BigDecimal.

      • NULL

        static final String NULL
